I have a created a session test for this and am able to reproduce the problem
but unfortuanately the right answer is complicated. 

Currently we are subclassing the internal runtime class EclipsePreferences (bug
54495) and doing a bunch of things to fit into that hierarchy. But project
preferences are special because they are stored in files which are managed by
the workspace and therefore sometimes receive deleted notification after the
fact, etc. So the right answer is to finally fix bug 54495 and put the #put,
#get, etc methods on the ProjectPreferences class. This will also clean up some
of the messiness of that code.

This is not a simple fix so I don't feel comfortable doing this for tomorrow's
milestone build but will release it for next week.
*** Bug 95816 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

I have decided the complexity of the fix for bug 54495 is too much for this
release at this point in the cycle. So rather than re-writing the hierarchy I
have fixed this bug directly and will fix the reference to the internal class
for 3.2.

Fix released to HEAD.
